<TITLE> Bangladesh go down against Mozambique in Malaysia </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 16 (bdnews24.com)  The Bangladesh national football team made a frustrating start in the Mardeka Cup with a 1-0 loss to the Mozambique U/20 side in the Malaysian capital of Kuala Lumpur on Thursday. "After the barren first half, Bangladesh went one goal down against Mozambique in the 87th minute," BFF vice president Badal Roy told bdnews24.com by telephone from Malaysia soon after the match. Francis scored the all-important goal three minutes from time. "They availed the lone opportunity though we dominated them throughout the game and produced a lot of scoring chances," Roy said. In the day's other Group B match, Vietnam's U/23 team handed a 3-1 defeat to Myanmar. Bangladesh will play their second match against Myanmar on Saturday before facing Vietnam in their last group match on Oct 20. b
